AI.description: The AI competitors will add logic to this AI so its functions return valid and smart values.

runTurn.description: This is called every time it is this AI.player's turn.

returns.description: Represents if you want to end your turn. True means end your turn, False means to keep your turn going and re-call this function.

branchesToCompleteLodge.description: How many branches a lodge must have to be considered complete.

currentPlayer.description: The player whose turn it is currently. That player can send commands. Other players cannot.

currentTurn.description: The current turn number, starting at 0 for the first player's turn.

freeBeaversCount.description: When a Player has less Beavers than this number, recruiting other Beavers is free.

gameObjects.description: A mapping of every game object's ID to the actual game object. Primarily used by the server and client to easily refer to the game objects via ID.

jobs.description: All the Jobs that Beavers can have in the game.

lodgesCompleteToWin.description: How many lodges must be complete at once to win the game.

mapHeight.description: The number of Tiles in the map along the y (vertical) axis.

mapWidth.description: The number of Tiles in the map along the x (horizontal) axis.

maxTurns.description: The maximum number of turns before the game will automatically end.

players.description: List of all the players in the game.

session.description: A unique identifier for the game instance that is being played.

spawnerTypes.description: All the types of spawners in the game.

tiles.description: All the tiles in the map, stored in Row-major order. Use `x + y * mapWidth` to access the correct index.

Game.description: Gather branches and build up your lodge as beavers fight to survive.
Game.name: Stumped

actions.description: The number of actions remaining for the beaver this turn.

branches.description: The number of branches this beaver is holding.

distracted.description: Number of turns this beaver is distracted for (0 means not distracted).

fish.description: The number of fish this beaver is holding.

health.description: How much health this beaver has left.

job.description: The Job this beaver was recruited to do.

moves.description: How many moves this beaver has left this turn.

owner.description: The Player that owns and can control this beaver.

tile.description: The tile this beaver is on.

arguments.description: The tile of the beaver you want to attack.
arguments.name: tile

returns.description: True if successfully attacked, false otherwise.

buildLodge.description: Builds a lodge on the Beavers current tile.

returns.description: True if successfully built a lodge, false otherwise.

arguments.description: The type of resource to drop ('branch' or 'fish').
arguments.name: resource

arguments.description: The amount of the resource to drop, numbers <= 0 will drop all of that type.
arguments.name: amount

drop.description: Drops some of the given resource on the beaver's tile. Fish dropped in water disappear instantly, and fish dropped on land die one per tile per turn.

returns.description: True if successfully dropped the resource, false otherwise.

arguments.description: The tile you want to harvest.
arguments.name: tile

harvest.description: Harvests the branches or fish from a Spawner on an adjacent tile.

returns.description: True if successfully harvested, false otherwise.

arguments.description: The tile this beaver should move to. Costs 2 moves normally, 3 if moving upstream, and 1 if moving downstream.
arguments.name: tile

move.description: Moves this beaver from its current tile to an adjacent tile.

returns.description: True if the move worked, false otherwise.

arguments.description: The type of resource to pickup ('branch' or 'fish').
arguments.name: resource

arguments.description: The amount of the resource to drop, numbers <= 0 will pickup all of that type.
arguments.name: amount

pickup.description: Picks up some branches or fish on the beaver's tile.

returns.description: True if successfully picked up a resource, false otherwise.

gameObjectName.description: String representing the top level Class that this game object is an instance of. Used for reflection to create new instances on clients, but exposed for convenience should AIs want this data.

id.description: A unique id for each instance of a GameObject or a sub class. Used for client and server communication. Should never change value after being set.

logs.description: Any strings logged will be stored here. Intended for debugging.

arguments.description: A string to add to this GameObject's log. Intended for debugging.
arguments.name: message

log.description: Adds a message to this GameObject's logs. Intended for your own debugging purposes, as strings stored here are saved in the gamelog.

actions.description: The number of actions this job can make per turn.

carryLimit.description: How many resources a beaver with this job can hold at once.

chopping.description: Scalar for how many branches this job harvests at once.

cost.description: How many fish this Job costs to recruit.

damage.description: The amount of damage this job does per attack.

distracts.description: How many turns a beaver attacked by this job is distracted by.

fishing.description: Scalar for how many fish this job harvests at once.

health.description: The amount of starting health this job has.

moves.description: The number of moves this job can make per turn.

arguments.description: The Tile that is a lodge owned by you that you wish to spawn the Beaver of this Job on.
arguments.name: lodge

recruit.description: Recruits a Beaver of this Job to a lodge

returns.description: The recruited Beaver if successful, null otherwise.

lost.description: If the player lost the game or not.

opponent.description: This player's opponent in the game.

reasonWon.description: The reason why the player won the game.

timeRemaining.description: The amount of time (in ns) remaining for this AI to send commands.

won.description: If the player won the game or not.

lodgeOwner.description: The owner of the beaver lodge on this tile, if present, otherwise null.

spawner.description: The resource spawner on this tile if present, otherwise null.

tileEast.description: The Tile to the 'East' of this one (x+1, y). Null if out of bounds of the map.

tileNorth.description: The Tile to the 'North' of this one (x, y-1). Null if out of bounds of the map.

tileSouth.description: The Tile to the 'South' of this one (x, y+1). Null if out of bounds of the map.

tileWest.description: The Tile to the 'West' of this one (x-1, y). Null if out of bounds of the map.

type.description: What type of Tile this is, either 'Water' or 'Land'.

x.description: The x (horizontal) position of this Tile.

y.description: The y (vertical) position of this Tile.
